    {
      "id": "PopularPost119856",
      "post_content": "I'm going to build a W/B lifegain deck with [Sanguine Bond](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sanguine Bond)... and I'm considering to put this quest instead of the [Rest for the Weary](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rest for the Weary)... I can just leave it in a play until I put Sanguine Bond and once it has it's counters, I don't need to put any other land for it to be effective... on the other hand, if you're finishing your game and draw this, it's in most cases quite disappointing. Not to mention that your opponent can easily prepare and react on every expedition...   \n  \nIt's not strictly worse or better then [Rest for the Weary](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rest for the Weary), they have just different usage... I will deffinitely try it, it can be really funny with things like [Elixir of Immortality](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Elixir of Immortality) and fetching lands",
      "posted_by": "Narim",
