      "post_content": "@armogohma - Then rarity is a factor. Acquiring a playset of these is much easier than of the Captain, and also take into account the amount of creature removal that is rampant.  \n  \nThe way I've always looked at it is that lifegain is white's way of stalling to the later game; blue has counter and bounce, black has destruction and graveyard shenanigans, red has burn (red doesn't really hope for late-game), and green has mass amounts of creatures.",
